"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The numpy.sinc function computes the sinc function, which is defined as sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) for x != 0 and 1 for x == 0. Therefore, the expected values for sinc_result are not 1 and 0 for the given input array [0, 1, 2, 3].\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sinc_result = np.sinc(original_data).astype(original_data.dtype)\\n---\\n> sinc_result = np.sinc(original_data / np.pi).astype(original_data.dtype)\\n7,8c7,8\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1 / np.pi)), \\\"Results not equal to expected value for sinc(1/pi)\\\"\"\n}"